    <h4 class="mt-5">UAT Test Scenarios</h4>
    <p>Use these accounts for the following UAT scenarios:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>UT01:</strong> Login and baseline access - Test all 4 demo accounts</li>
        <li><strong>UT02:</strong> RBAC enforcement - Test Admissions and Cashier accounts</li>
        <li><strong>UT03:</strong> Create sponsor record - Use Admin or Admissions account</li>
        <li><strong>UT04:</strong> Validation and error messaging - Use Admin or Admissions account</li>
        <li><strong>UT05:</strong> Update sponsor record - Use Admin or Admissions account</li>
        <li><strong>UT06:</strong> Duplicate detection and merge - Use Admin account with DEMO-SP001 and DEMO-SP006</li>
        <li><strong>UT07:</strong> Submit change request - Use Admissions account</li>
        <li><strong>UT08:</strong> Apply change request - Use Admin account</li>
        <li><strong>UT09:</strong> LoG list and coverage access - Use Admin or Admissions account</li>
        <li><strong>UT10:</strong> Audit retrieval - Use Admin account</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="mt-4">
        <a href="@Url.Action("UATScripts", "PilotSupport")" class="btn btn-primary">
            <i class="bi bi-clipboard-check"></i> View UAT Scripts
        </a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("TestData", "PilotSupport")" class="btn btn-outline-primary">
            <i class="bi bi-database"></i> View All Test Data
        </a>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    function copyPassword(elementId) {
        const element = document.getElementById(elementId);
        const text = element.innerText;
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
            alert('Password copied to clipboard: ' + text);
        }).catch(err => {
            console.error('Failed to copy: ', err);
        });
    }
</script>
